properties.name: FogHeight
properties.comment: The ZValue of the fog

properties.name: FogDensity
properties.comment: Density of the fog

properties.name: FullyDirectionalInscatteringColorDistance
properties.comment: Distance at which InscatteringColorCubemap should be used directly for the Inscattering Color.

properties.name: NonDirectionalInscatteringColorDistance
properties.comment: Distance at which only the average color of InscatteringColorCubemap should be used as Inscattering Color.

properties.name: DirectionalInscatteringExponent
properties.comment:
Controls the size of the directional inscattering cone, which is used to approximate inscattering from a directional light.
Note: there must be a directional light with bUsedAsAtmosphereSunLight enabled for DirectionalInscattering to be used.

properties.name: DirectionalInscatteringStartDistance
properties.comment:
Controls the start distance from the viewer of the directional inscattering, which is used to approximate inscattering from a directional light.
Note: there must be a directional light with bUsedAsAtmosphereSunLight enabled for DirectionalInscattering to be used.

properties.name: DirectionalInscatteringColor
properties.comment:
Controls the color of the directional inscattering, which is used to approximate inscattering from a directional light.
Note: there must be a directional light with bUsedAsAtmosphereSunLight enabled for DirectionalInscattering to be used.

properties.name: FogHeightFalloff
properties.comment:
Height density factor, controls how the density increases as height decreases.
Smaller values make the visible transition larger.

properties.name: FogMaxOpacity
properties.comment:
A value of 1 means the fog can become fully opaque at a distance and replace scene color completely,
A value of 0 means the fog color will not be factored in at all.

properties.name: StartDistance
properties.comment: Distance from the camera that the fog will start, in world units.

properties.name: FogCutoffDistance
properties.comment: Scene elements past this distance will not have fog applied.  This is useful for excluding skyboxes which already have fog baked in.
